COLORSCHEMES / THEMES

There are a number of different colorschemes locally available.
To see all the ready-to-use colorschemes, open any file with the vim editor and write :colorscheme [space] [Ctrl + d]
To set the colorscheme write :colorscheme <name_of_the_colorscheme> and hit enter to see the changes
for example, :colorscheme delek
There is also a colorscheme named default
To check the present colorscheme, write :colorscheme and hit enter

Downloaded the molokai colorscheme using the three following commands
mkdir ~/.vim/colors
cd ~/.vim/colors
curl -o molokai.vim https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tomasr/molokai/master/colors/molokai.vim

Then permanently set the colorscheme molokai in the .vimrc file

vim-plug is installed using
curl -fLo ~/.vim/autoload/plug.vim --create-dirs \
    https://raw.githubusercontent.com/junegunn/vim-plug/master/plug.vim
